# Loop Constraints — {{REPO_NAME}}

> The C31 loop reads this file at the start of EVERY run.
> Constraints here are BINDING — the loop MUST follow them without exception.

## Hard Stops (Never Do)

- Never auto-merge to main without human approval
- Never edit `.env`, `.env.*`, `secrets/`, `credentials/`, `auth/`
- Never disable tests to make CI green
- Never push directly to main/master
- Never spend more than {{BUDGET_TOKENS}} tokens in a single run

## Escalation Triggers (Stop Loop + Notify Human)

- Same type of error occurs 3 consecutive times → write FAILED to STATE.md, halt
- Any change touching authentication, payments, or security → require human review
- Ambiguous task with no clear success criterion → ask human before acting

## Allowed Actions (No Human Approval Needed)

- Read any file in the repository
- Create draft PRs (not merge)
- Write to STATE.md, loop-run-log.md
- Create GitHub Issues (for escalation only)
- Run tests in read-only mode

## Allowed With Caution (Log Every Action)

- Edit files in non-critical paths
- Install/update patch-level dependencies
- Create new branches (prefix: `loop/`)

